'''The Internationalist League of Norway''' ({{lang-no|Forbundet Internasjonalen i Noreg}} (FIN) is a group of revolutionary socialists, set up in 1999,<ref>{{cite web|title=Leftist Parties of Norway|url=http://www.broadleft.org/no.htm|publisher=Broad Left|accessdate=8 May 2016}}</ref> working in sympathy with the [[Reunified Fourth International|Fourth International]]. Until 2002 FIN worked as a current within the [[Red Electoral Alliance]] advocating that the Red Electoral Alliance should be a broad party for revolutionaries on Norway, based on internationalism, anti-stalinism and internal democracy. Since 2002 FIN operates both within the Red Electoral Alliance and the [[Socialist Left Party (Norway)|Socialist Left Party]].

